It seems that there is a concerted attempt by some to denigrate military accomplishments at the expense of the men who won their awards.  Their heroism seems to deminish those who choose not to participate, and rather than celebrate the individual accomplishments, these people attempt to deny that they occurred.  Does this make sense to any of you?
